profile_positions.description:
Liaison between the European Police Mission in Afghanistan, CPCC, DG RELEX en CSO. This aims at achieving Mission’s goals, in all the related matters such as logistics, transport, finance, procurement, medical, engineering, human resources, ICT en regional deployment, Legal and Financial Control and General Administration. Tasks and responsibilities include amongst other:

- Assist the Head of Mission in the process of defining and addressing the overall Mission Support related requirements of the Mission;
- Participate in the recruitment, selection, deployment and rotation of international staff;
- Establish and maintain contacts with Contributing States facilitating the participation of their nationals to the Mission;
- Participate in the assessment of the costs of covering the needs of the Mission, liaising with the EU Commission and actors providing support to the Mission;
- Facilitate linkages with the contracted bank;
- Establish and maintain contacts with the Commission services and other relevant institutions and organisations on Mission Support related matters;
- Provide induction training, advice and assistance on all Mission Support related issues to Mission personnel;
- Participate in the preparation of Mission Support related plans and reports.

Management of the support element of the European Police Mission in Afghanistan including 60 international and 130 Afghan staff members in the departments of Administration, General Support Services, Documents and Records; ISAF liaison; and Regional Support. Tasks and responsibilities include amongst other:

• Member of the Mission’s Senior Management Team;
• Command and coordination of the branch and support and advise to Mission Command, as well as development of inter-unit plans and coordination, setting goals and deadlines and defining procedures and responsibilities;
• Lead the process to define and address the global administrative requirements of the mission including, inter alia, finance and budgetary requirements, human resources, procurement and logistics;
• Lead the staff responsible for the effective security and control of designated funds allocated to the mission and all necessary internal and external administrative and support functions;
• Monitor and direct day-to-day administrative and support operations of the ESDP Mission, as well as to lead the preparation of all related reports, including figures, statistics, inventories and analysis of current and future requirements;
• Assist and advise with the assistance of the appropriate technical staff, on all administrative, personnel, financial and logistical issues;
• Lead the staff responsible for providing training and assistance to the mission members related with all administrative, personnel and finance matters;
• Lead the process of developing suitable induction training packages on administrative matters for new members;
• Study and propose operational and management decisions that have the objective to increase the efficiency of the mission;
• Produce, co-ordinate and decide about plans and reports related with the mission activities, namely related with the organisation and administrative services.

Process- and financial management of programmes and projects funded by the European Union from Structural Fund recourses under the European Fund for Regional Development and the European Social Fund e.g. the Community Initiatives INTERREG and EQUAL, Innovative Action Programmes, and Objective 2 and 3 programmes.
Assignments were covering the whole lifecycle of programmes and projects e.g. preparation, application, implementation, winding up and closure, and could include: 
- Programme and Project management and coordination;
- Managing international partnerships;
- Implementation Audit and Control systems;
- Financial-, legal-, and management advise;
- Internal and external reporting on activities and expenditures;
- Liaison between international partners;
- Contacts with Programme-Secretariats/ European Commission;
- Co-ordination between policy and financial departments;
- Training sessions and presentations on process- and financial management.

- Contacts with placement providers;
- Liaison in between the institute, students and assignment providers;
- Setting up and implementation of a (financial) control system for European Union grants (Leonardo da Vinci/Erasmus).
